{{Unreferenced|date=May 2008}}

'''Noel Synnott''' (born [[1952]] in London) is a former football player from [[Ireland]].

He was a defender who played for [[Shamrock Rovers]] and played 3 times for the [[Republic of Ireland national football team]] in 1978.

He began in the [[Football League of Ireland|League of Ireland]] in 1973 playing for Sligo Rovers. He joined Shamrock Rovers the following year firstly playing under Mick Meagan, then [[Sean Thomas]] and [[John Giles]]. He played for nine years at [[Milltown]], making 4 appearances in European competition and an Inter League cap, before disaster struck on the 27th of March 1983 when he broke his leg in a league game against Dundalk.

Doctors told him he would never play again but 2 years later he made a comeback for [[Waterford United]] where he scored an own goal in the [[FAI Cup]] Final in 1986 against Rovers!

After his playing career ended he served as manager of [[Kilkenny City F.C.]] and Shamrock Rovers for a brief period in 2004.

==Honours==
* ''' [[FAI Cup]]''': 1
** [[Shamrock Rovers]] 1978
* '''[[FAI League Cup]]''': 1
** [[Shamrock Rovers]] - 1976/77
* '''[[Leinster Senior Cup (football)]]''': 1
** [[Shamrock Rovers]] - 1982

